
[1]sublimity

   SUBLIM'ITY, n. [L. sublimitas.]

   1. Elevation of place; lofty highth.

   2. Highth in excellence; loftiness of nature or character;

            moral grandeur; as God's incomprehensible sublimity.

   The sublimity of the character of Christ owes nothing to his
   historians.

   3. In oratory and composition, lofty conceptions, or such conceptions
   expressed in corresponding language; loftiness of sentiment or style.

   Milton's distinguishing excellence lies in the sublimity of his
   thoughts.
